<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-16T10:16:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-16T10:16:00-05:00" n="337" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d337">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3862</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SFJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-16T11:00:00-04:16">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 1.10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Argentine answer to Brazil note published yesterday says that the
                                Argentine Government which has just pronounced its judgment with
                                respect to, and in defense of, the principles of universal
                                international law, duly appreciates the attitude assumed by Brazil,
                                based exactly on those conceptions, and expresses to her its
                                frankest sentiments of cofraternity.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SFJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>